## Requirements

* Bash 4+
* MySQL or MariaDB
* dialog

Install dependencies:

```bash
sudo apt install dialog mysql-client
```

---

## Getting Started

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/bash-db-manager.git
cd bash-db-manager
chmod +x app.sh
./app.sh
```

---

## Authentication

When starting the application, you will be prompted to enter:

* Database host
* Username
* Database name
* Password

Credentials are **not stored anywhere** and are only used during the active session.

